<paragraph blockId="63.[151,1436,586,986]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
The only species in this genus currently known from South America is 
<taxonomicName authority="Kieffer &amp; Jorgensen (Kieffer &amp; Jorgensen, 1910)" authorityName="Kieffer &amp; Jorgensen (Kieffer &amp; Jorgensen" authorityYear="1910" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Opisthoscelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prosopidis">
<emphasis box="[1018,1180,586,611]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">O. prosopidis</emphasis>
Kieffer &amp; Jorgensen (
<bibRefCitation author="Kieffer, J. J. &amp; Jorgensen, P." box="[159,498,624,650]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="362 - 444" refId="ref50514" refString="Kieffer, J. J. &amp; Jorgensen, P. (1910) Gallen und Gallentiere aus Argentinien. Zentralblatt fur Bakteriologie, Parasitenkunde, Infektionskrankheiten (und Hygiene). Jena, 27, 362 - 444." type="journal article" year="1910">Kieffer &amp; Jorgensen, 1910</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[522,689,624,649]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Opisthoscelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[522,689,624,649]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Opisthoscelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
currently contains 15 species, all of which are restricted to 
<collectingCountry box="[151,265,661,687]" name="Australia" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Australia</collectingCountry>
apart from 
<emphasis box="[415,592,661,686]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kieffer &amp; Jorgensen (Kieffer &amp; Jorgensen" authorityYear="1910" box="[415,587,661,686]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Opisthoscelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prosopidis">O. prosopidis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
which is known only from the original description from 
<collectingCountry box="[1312,1435,661,687]" name="Argentina" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(Aragon, Alto Pencoso, on 
<taxonomicName box="[477,728,698,723]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Prosopis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="adesmiodes">
<emphasis box="[477,728,698,723]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Prosopis adesmiodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). As pointed out by Lizer y 
<bibRefCitation author="Trelles, C. A." box="[1068,1239,698,724]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="157 - 210" refId="ref51001" refString="Lizer y Trelles, C. A. (1939) Catalogo sistematico razonado de los coccidos (Hom. Sternor) vernaculos de la Argentina. Physis. Buenos Aires, 17: 157 - 210." type="journal article" year="1939">Trelles (1939)</bibRefCitation>
, the species was only placed in this genus tentatively by Kieffer &amp; Jorgensen and, on the basis of the original description and on the distribution of the other species in the genus, Lizer y Trellis did not believe that this species belonged to 
<taxonomicName box="[151,311,810,835]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Opisthoscelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,311,810,835]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Opisthoscelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This was also the view of 
<bibRefCitation author="Hoy, J. M." box="[643,785,810,836]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="1 - 260" refId="ref50426" refString="Hoy, J. M. (1963) A Catalogue of the Eriococcidae (Homoptera: Coccoidea) of the world. New Zealand Department of Scientific and Industrial Research Bulletin, 150, 1 - 260." type="journal article" year="1963">Hoy (1963)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Miller, D. R. &amp; Gimpel, M. E." box="[798,1088,810,836]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" refId="ref51225" refString="Miller, D. R. &amp; Gimpel, M. E. (2000) A Systematic Catalogue of the Eriococcidae (Felt Scales) (Hemiptera: Coccoidea) of the World. Intercept, Andover, UK, 589 pp." type="book" year="2000">Miller &amp; Gimpel (2000)</bibRefCitation>
state that the 
<typeStatus box="[1257,1308,810,836]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">type</typeStatus>
status and 
<typeStatus box="[151,201,848,874]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">type</typeStatus>
designation are unknown, and no depository is known. The original description does have an illustration of the gall and it may be possible in the future to clarify the identity of this species by finding similar galls on 
<taxonomicName box="[151,346,922,948]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Prosopis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[151,254,922,947]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Prosopis</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in the 
<typeStatus box="[426,477,922,948]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">type</typeStatus>
locality. Until such time, it is felt best to assume that this species is unidentifiable and that it is unlikely to belong to 
<taxonomicName authority="Schrader." authorityName="Schrader." box="[553,828,960,986]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Opisthoscelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[553,711,960,985]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Opisthoscelis</emphasis>
Schrader.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
